{"type":"message","id":"d17bd390","parentId":"8a15e64b","timestamp":"2026-03-25T01:14:59.183Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_V3zU9oJR65l30qDJ0RPc4QRc|fc_0c4adb51b76bd9770169c3371598f88191832e695a7264e086","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"C:\\Users\\Gustavo\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\docs.json:145: \"destination\": \"/providers/openai\"\r\nC:\\Users\\Gustavo\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\docs.json:149: \"destination\": \"/providers/openai\"\r\nC:\\Users\\Gustavo\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\docs.json:1201: \"providers/openai\",\r\nC:\\Users\\Gustavo\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\docs.json:1814: \"zh-CN/providers/openai\",\r\nC:\\Users\\Gustavo\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\tts.md:12: OpenClaw can convert outbound replies into audio using ElevenLabs, Microsoft, or OpenAI.\r\nC:\\Users\\Gustavo\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\tts.md:52: - [OpenAI Audio API reference](https://platform.openai.com/docs/api-reference/audio)\r\nC:\\Users\\Gustavo\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\tts.md:91: provider: \"openai\",\r\nC:\\Users\\Gustavo\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\tts.md:210: - `provider`: speech provider id such as `\"elevenlabs\"`, `\"microsoft\"`, or `\"openai\"` (fallback is automatic).\r\nC:\\Users\\Gustavo\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\tts.md:211: - If `provider` is **unset**, OpenClaw prefers `openai` (if key), then `elevenlabs` (if key),\r\nC:\\Users\\Gustavo\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\tts.md:267: - `provider` (registered speech provider id, for example `openai`, `elevenlabs`, or `microsoft`; requires `allowProvider: true`)\r\nC:\\Users\\Gustavo\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\tts.md:377: /tts provider openai\r\nC:\\Users\\Gustavo\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\channels\\discord.md:1042: provider: \"openai\",\r\nC:\\Users\\Gustavo\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\cli\\config.md:78: --provider-arg openai/api-key \\\r\nC:\\Users\\Gustavo\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\cli\\config.md:155: --provider-arg openai/api-key \\\r\nC:\\Users\\Gustavo\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\cli\\index.md:700: - Providers: Anthropic, GitHub Copilot, OpenAI Codex OAuth, plus Gemini CLI via the bundled `google` plugin and Antigravity where configured.\r\nC:\\Users\\Gustavo\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\cli\\onboard.md:72: - Set the provider env var in the onboarding process environment (for example `OPENAI_API_KEY`).\r\nC:\\Users\\Gustavo\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\cli\\onboard.md:145: - Custom Provider: connect any OpenAI or Anthropic compatible endpoint,\r\nC:\\Users\\Gustavo\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\concepts\\compaction.md:98: See [OpenAI provider](/providers/openai) for model params and overrides.\r\nC:\\Users\\Gustavo\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\concepts\\features.md:51: - 35+ model providers (Anthropic, OpenAI, Google, and more)\r\nC:\\Users\\Gustavo\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\concepts\\features.md:53: - Custom and self-hosted provider support (vLLM, SGLang, Ollama, and any OpenAI-compatible or Anthropic-compatible endpoint)\r\nC:\\Users\\Gustavo\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\concepts\\memory.md:100: Memory search supports multiple embedding providers (OpenAI, Gemini, Voyage,\r\nC:\\Users\\Gustavo\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\concepts\\model-providers.md:114: The bundled `openai` plugin now owns both provider ids: `openai` and\r\nC:\\Users\\Gustavo\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\concepts\\model-providers.md:142: - Provider: `openai`\r\nC:\\Users\\Gustavo\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\concepts\\model-providers.md:179: - Provider: `openai-codex`\r\nC:\\Users\\Gustavo\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\concepts\\model-providers.md:182: - CLI: `openclaw onboard --auth-choice openai-codex` or `openclaw models auth login --provider openai-codex`\r\nC:\\Users\\Gustavo\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\concepts\\model-providers.md:497: vLLM ships as a bundled provider plugin for local/self-hosted OpenAI-compatible\r\nC:\\Users\\Gustavo\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\concepts\\models.md:46: It can set up model + auth for common providers, including **OpenAI Code (Codex)\r\nC:\\Users\\Gustavo\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\concepts\\oauth.md:13: OpenClaw supports \"subscription auth\" via OAuth for providers that offer it (notably **OpenAI Codex (ChatGPT OAuth)**). For Anthropic subscriptions, use the **setup-token** flow. Anthropic subscription use outside Claude Code has been restricted for some users in the past, so treat it as a user-choice risk and verify current Anthropic policy yourself. OpenAI Codex OAuth is explicitly supported for use in external tools like OpenClaw. This page explains:\r\nC:\\Users\\Gustavo\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\gateway\\configuration-examples.md:76: \"openai:default\": { provider: \"openai\", mode: \"api_key\" },\r\nC:\\Users\\Gustavo\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\gateway\\configuration-examples.md:77: \"openai-codex:default\": { provider: \"openai-codex\", mode: \"oauth\" },\r\nC:\\Users\\Gustavo\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\gateway\\configuration-examples.md:140: { provider: \"openai\", model: \"gpt-4o-mini-transcribe\" },\r\nC:\\Users\\Gustavo\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\gateway\\configuration-reference.md:290: provider: \"openai\",\r\nC:\\Users\\Gustavo\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\gateway\\configuration-reference.md:908: - If you select a provider/model directly, configure the matching provider auth/API key too (for example `GEMINI_API_KEY` or `GOOGLE_API_KEY` for `google/*`, `OPENAI_API_KEY` for `openai/*`, `FAL_KEY` for `fal/*`).\r\nC:\\Users\\Gustavo\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\gateway\\configuration-reference.md:1286: providers: [\"openai\"], // optional\r\nC:\\Users\\Gustavo\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\gateway\\configuration-reference.md:1956: { provider: \"openai\", model: \"gpt-4o-mini-transcribe\" },\r\nC:\\Users\\Gustavo\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\gateway\\configuration-reference.md:1974: - `provider`: API provider id (`openai`, `anthropic`, `google`/`gemini`, `groq`, etc.)\r\nC:\\Users\\Gustavo\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\gateway\\configuration-reference.md:1985: - `capabilities`: optional list (`image`, `audio`, `video`). Defaults: `openai`/`anthropic`/`minimax`  image, `google`  image+audio+video, `groq`  audio.\r\nC:\\Users\\Gustavo\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\gateway\\configuration-reference.md:2129: - `models.providers.*.api`: request adapter (`openai-completions`, `openai-responses`, `anthropic-messages`, `google-generative-ai`, etc).\r\nC:\\Users\\Gustavo\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\gateway\\configuration-reference.md:2132: - `models.providers.*.injectNumCtxForOpenAICompat`: for Ollama + `openai-completions`, inject `options.num_ctx` into requests (default: `true`).\r\nC:\\Users\\Gustavo\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\gateway\\configuration-reference.md:2137: - `models.providers.*.models.*.compat.supportsDeveloperRole`: optional compatibility hint. For `api: \"openai-completions\"` with a non-empty non-native `baseUrl` (host not `api.openai.com`), OpenClaw forces this to `false` at runtime. Empty/omitted `baseUrl` keeps default OpenAI behavior.\r\nC:\\Users\\Gustavo\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\gateway\\configuration-reference.md:2854: - `source: \"file\"` id: absolute JSON pointer (for example `\"/providers/openai/apiKey\"`)\r\nC:\\Users\\Gustavo\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\gateway\\configuration.md:595: openai: { apiKey: { source: \"env\", provider: \"default\", id: \"OPENAI_API_KEY\" } },\r\nC:\\Users\\Gustavo\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\gateway\\doctor.md:124: - `routing.transcribeAudio`  `tools.media.audio.models`\r\nC:\\Users\\Gustavo\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\gateway\\local-models.md:14: If you want the lowest-friction local setup, start with [Ollama](/providers/ollama) and `openclaw onboard`. This page is the opinionated guide for higher-end local stacks and custom OpenAI-compatible local servers.\r\nC:\\Users\\Gustavo\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\gateway\\openshell.md:202: providers: [\"openai\"],\r\nC:\\Users\\Gustavo\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\gateway\\sandbox-vs-tool-policy-vs-elevated.md:68: Provider tool keys accept either `provider` (e.g. `google-antigravity`) or `provider/model` (e.g. `openai/gpt-5.2`).\r\nC:\\Users\\Gustavo\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\gateway\\secrets-plan-contract.md:27: path: \"models.providers.openai.apiKey\",\r\nC:\\Users\\Gustavo\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\gateway\\secrets-plan-contract.md:28: pathSegments: [\"models\", \"providers\", \"openai\", \"apiKey\"],\r\nC:\\Users\\Gustavo\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\gateway\\secrets-plan-contract.md:29: providerId: \"openai\",\r\nC:\\Users\\Gustavo\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\gateway\\secrets-plan-contract.md:30: ref: { source: \"env\", provider: \"default\", id: \"OPENAI_API_KEY\" },\r\nC:\\Users\\Gustavo\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\gateway\\secrets-plan-contract.md:37: ref: { source: \"env\", provider: \"default\", id: \"OPENAI_API_KEY\" },\r\nC:\\Users\\Gustavo\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\gateway\\secrets-plan-contract.md:79: Invalid plan target path for models.providers.apiKey: models.providers.openai.baseUrl\r\nC:\\Users\\Gustavo\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\gateway\\secrets.md:90: { source: \"env\", provider: \"default\", id: \"OPENAI_API_KEY\" }\r\nC:\\Users\\Gustavo\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\gateway\\secrets.md:101: { source: \"file\", provider: \"filemain\", id: \"/providers/openai/apiKey\" }\r\nC:\\Users\\Gustavo\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\gateway\\secrets.md:113: { source: \"exec\", provider: \"vault\", id: \"providers/openai/apiKey\" }\r\nC:\\Users\\Gustavo\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\gateway\\secrets.md:183: { \"protocolVersion\": 1, \"provider\": \"vault\", \"ids\": [\"providers/openai/apiKey\"] }\r\nC:\\Users\\Gustavo\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\gateway\\secrets.md:189: { \"protocolVersion\": 1, \"values\": { \"providers/openai/apiKey\": \"<openai-api-key>\" } } // pragma: allowlist secret\r\nC:\\Users\\Gustavo\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\gateway\\secrets.md:198: \"errors\": { \"providers/openai/apiKey\": { \"message\": \"not found\" } }\r\nC:\\Users\\Gustavo\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\gateway\\secrets.md:226: apiKey: { source: \"exec\", provider: \"onepassword_openai\", id: \"value\" },\r\nC:\\Users\\Gustavo\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\gateway\\secrets.md:255: apiKey: { source: \"exec\", provider: \"vault_openai\", id: \"value\" },\r\nC:\\Users\\Gustavo\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\gateway\\secrets.md:273: args: [\"-d\", \"--extract\", '[\"providers\"][\"openai\"][\"apiKey\"]', \"/path/to/secrets.enc.json\"],\r\nC: