models auth login --provider openai-codex`\r\nC:\\Users\\Gustavo\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\concepts\\model-providers.md:497: vLLM ships as a bundled provider plugin for local/self-hosted OpenAI-compatible\r\nC:\\Users\\Gustavo\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\concepts\\models.md:46: It can set up model + auth for common providers, including **OpenAI Code (Codex)\r\nC:\\Users\\Gustavo\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\concepts\\oauth.md:13: OpenClaw supports \"subscription auth\" via OAuth for providers that offer it (notably **OpenAI Codex (ChatGPT OAuth)**). For Anthropic subscriptions, use the **setup-token** flow. Anthropic subscription use outside Claude Code has been restricted for some users in the past, so treat it as a user-choice risk and verify current Anthropic policy yourself. OpenAI Codex OAuth is explicitly supported for use in external tools like OpenClaw. This page explains:\r\nC:\\Users\\Gustavo\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\gateway\\configuration-examples.md:76: \"openai:default\": { provider: \"openai\", mode: \"api_key\" },\r\nC:\\Users\\Gustavo\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\gateway\\configuration-examples.md:77: \"openai-codex:default\": { provider: \"openai-codex\", mode: \"oauth\" },\r\nC:\\Users\\Gustavo\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\gateway\\configuration-examples.md:140: { provider: \"openai\", model: \"gpt-4o-mini-transcribe\" },\r\nC:\\Users\\Gustavo\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\gateway\\configuration-reference.md:290: provider: \"openai\",\r\nC:\\Users\\Gustavo\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\gateway\\configuration-reference.md:908: - If you select a provider/model directly, configure the matching provider auth/API key too (for example `GEMINI_API_KEY` or `GOOGLE_API_KEY` for `google/*`, `OPENAI_API_KEY` for `openai/*`, `FAL_KEY` for `fal/*`).\r\nC:\\Users\\Gustavo\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\gateway\\configuration-reference.md:1286: providers: [\"openai\"], // optional\r\nC:\\Users\\Gustavo\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\gateway\\configuration-reference.md:1956: { provider: \"openai\", model: \"gpt-4o-mini-transcribe\" },\r\nC:\\Users\\Gustavo\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\gateway\\configuration-reference.md:1974: - `provider`: API provider id (`openai`, `anthropic`, `google`/`gemini`, `groq`, etc.)\r\nC:\\Users\\Gustavo\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\gateway\\configuration-reference.md:1985: - `capabilities`: optional list (`image`, `audio`, `video`). Defaults: `openai`/`anthropic`/`minimax`  image, `google`  image+audio+video, `groq`  audio.\r\nC:\\Users\\Gustavo\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\gateway\\configuration-reference.md:2129: - `models.providers.*.api`: request adapter (`openai-completions`, `openai-responses`, `anthropic-messages`, `google-generative-ai`, etc).\r\nC:\\Users\\Gustavo\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\gateway\\configuration-reference.md:2132: - `models.providers.*.injectNumCtxForOpenAICompat`: for Ollama + `openai-completions`, inject `options.num_ctx` into requests (default: `true`).\r\nC:\\Users\\Gustavo\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\gateway\\configuration-reference.md:2137: - `models.providers.*.models.*.compat.supportsDeveloperRole`: optional compatibility hint. For `api: \"openai-completions\"` with a non-empty non-native `baseUrl` (host not `api.openai.com`), OpenClaw forces this to `false` at runtime. Empty/omitted `baseUrl` keeps default OpenAI behavior.\r\nC:\\Users\\Gustavo\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\\openclaw\\docs\\gateway\\configuration-reference.md:2854: - `source: \"file\"` id: absolute JSON pointer (for example `\"/providers/openai/apiKey\"`)\r\nC:\\Users\\Gustavo\\AppData\\Roaming\\npm\\node_modules\